<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-07-0965 </DOCNO><TEXT>This handbook provides unique insights into EPA procedures and for handlingRCRA and Superfund cases. The Handbook details how EPA identifies enforcementcases for judicial action; types of relief available; when to recommendjudicial instead of administrative actions; roles and responsibilitiesin making enforcement decisions; developing pre-referral cases; preparingreferral packages; managing cases; negotiations; settlements; trial;and more. Corporate counsels, law firms whose clients experience RCRA/CERCLAlegal problems, and organizations subject to RCRA/CERLA regulations benefitfrom learning first-hand how EPA processes cases.</TEXT></DOC>